programme.title: Patricia Routledge Remembers
programme.desc: Miss Pyms Day Out saw Patricia Routledge portray legendary author Barbara Pym in an RTS Award-winning episode of Bookmark, set on the day of the 1977 Booker Prize Awards, of which Pyms Quartet in Autumn was nominated. The novel marked a huge revival and interest in Pyms work after 16 years, and in this introduction, Patricia gives us a sense of what it was like to tell this incredible story, from the encounters with Pyms family that were involved in the project.

programme.title: Bookmark
programme.desc: Dramatised documentary about the writer Barbara Pym, depicting one day in her life - 23 November 1977 - when she travelled to London to attend the Booker Prize ceremony. Patricia Routledge plays Barbara Pym.

programme.title: Patricia Routledge Remembers
programme.desc: Talking Heads was Alan Bennetts acclaimed series of one-off tele-plays, written specifically for a selection of some of his favourite actors, including the great Patricia Routledge. Here, Patricia recalls what it was like to receive the scripts that were so perfectly suited to her comic abilities: A Woman of No Importance, A Lady of Letters and Miss Fozzard Finds Her Feet. She describes the challenges of bringing three unique characters to life for television.

programme.title: Talking Heads

programme.title: Tom Kerridges America
programme.desc: Tom Kerridge travels to Colorado to find out why its residents are some of the fittest in America. He makes his own stamp on traditional Venezuelan Arepas.

programme.title: Tom Kerridges America
programme.desc: Tom Kerridge travels to Californias Central Valley to experience fantastic food. He bakes a delicious walnut and orange cake and harvests asparagus.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Its an all-lady quarter-final as the remaining five have to impress with their dessert skills. In the signature bake, judges Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood are expecting to see and taste baked cheesecakes that reach their high expectations. The technical challenge is the bete noir of most bakers - a chocolate roulade. Finally, hundreds of choux pastry profiteroles must be perfected.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Its semi-final time and the four remaining bakers must prove they are worth a place in the final. The signature challenge requires them to make a baked, layered, mousse cake. The technical challenge is Pauls favourite sweet treat - iced fingers. Finally, the bakers must produce a batch of three different types of pastries or croissants.

programme.title: The Hairy Bikers Go West

programme.title: The Hairy Bikers Go Local
programme.desc: Bobby and Minal have built up a loyal customer base, winning a host of awards along the way, including a prestigious Michelin Bib Gourmand. But now they have their eyes on an even bigger prize, a coveted Michelin star.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: This trip Guys chasing down the holiday meal every which way. In Portland, Maine, we visit a family-run joint where stuffed turkey and stuffed lobster are Thanksgiving traditions.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieri visits Americas most interesting and unique restaurants. In Minnesota, Guy has banana cream pie and bison pot roast, a French toast leg of lamb in Virginia, and coconut curry in California.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieri visits Americas most interesting and unique restaurants. Guy visits a Mexican cafe in New Jersey for chicken wings, a pizza spot in Idaho, and a Jamaican place in Nashville.
